OU Career Documents & Interview Analyst
Technology-Focused Career AI
Overview
The OU Career Documents & Interview Analyst is an AI-powered career support tool designed for technology majors and early-career professionals. It assists students with resume development, role fit evaluation, interview preparation, and job compensation analysis while enforcing strict standards for accuracy, ethics, and verification.
This tool is intended to support students—not replace personal judgment, writing ability, or professional responsibility.
________________________________________
Who This GPT Is For
This GPT is designed specifically for technology-related majors and roles, including but not limited to:
•	Computer Science
•	Software Engineering
•	Information Technology
•	Cybersecurity
•	Data Science
•	Related technical disciplines
It is not a general-purpose career tool for all majors.
________________________________________
Core Capabilities
Resume Generation (ATS-Compliant)
The GPT helps students generate Applicant Tracking System (ATS)- compliant resumes using only verified, user-provided information.
Key features:
•	Text-only, ATS-safe formatting
•	Role-aligned structure and content
•	Strict formatting and layout standards
•	STAR-aligned bullet points
•	No fabrication, estimation, or inflated claims
________________________________________
Location & Role Fit Assessment
When a job description is provided, the GPT evaluates:
1.	Location compatibility (remote, hybrid, on-site, relocation constraints)
2.	Role fit score (0–100) based on skills, experience, education, and alignment
Output includes:
•	Location fit classification
•	One-line fit score and recommendation:
o	Apply or Do Not Apply
________________________________________
Interview Preparation
The GPT supports interview readiness by providing:
•	Role-specific technical questions
•	Behavioral questions using the STAR method
•	“Tell me about yourself” guidance
•	Questions students can ask interviewers
A mock interview mode is available, where responses are reviewed for clarity, structure, relevance, accuracy, and conciseness.
________________________________________
Job Compensation & Financial Analysis
The GPT provides data-informed compensation guidance for technology roles, including:
•	Typical salary ranges (when verifiable data is available)
•	Offer breakdown and comparison
•	Context around location, role scope, and experience level
•	Ethical negotiation preparation
The GPT does not speculate, fabricate figures, or provide deceptive negotiation advice.
________________________________________
Resume Formatting Standards (Enforced)
All resumes generated by this GPT follow these required standards:
•	Margins: 0.3 inches (top, bottom, left, right)
•	Line spacing: Single
•	Font: Times New Roman (preferred, optional)
•	Candidate name: Bold, font size 16
•	All headers and subheaders: Bold
•	Experience entries:
o	Job title, company, location, and dates bolded
•	Exactly three bullet points per role
•	Resume length: 1–3 pages
________________________________________
Education & Transcript Handling
If a student uploads an unofficial transcript, the GPT will:
•	Extract verified education details
•	Include GPA and graduation date if present
•	Add a Relevant Coursework section using exact course titles
•	Avoid inferring or renaming coursework
If no transcript is provided, coursework is not added.
________________________________________
Cover Letter Guidance & AI Usage Policy
How the GPT Helps
The GPT may assist with:
•	Cover letter structure and outline
•	Identifying role-aligned themes
•	Reviewing clarity and relevance
•	Providing checklists and guidance
IMPORTANT WARNING ABOUT AI-GENERATED COVER LETTERS
Cover letters are increasingly used by employers to detect AI-generated content.
Under no circumstances should students submit an AI-generated cover letter verbatim.
Doing so may result in automatic rejection.
Students should:
•	Use AI for guidance only
•	Write the final cover letter in their own words
•	Ensure authenticity and personal voice
The student is fully responsible for all submitted materials.
________________________________________
